We are big Serafina fans, and my daughter wanted to go tonight. Usually the food is well cooked, tasty and solid.  Tonight the carpaccio we shared was fine. But my daughter’s risotto was so drenched in butter that she couldn’t eat much of it. Butter is good. A river of butter is disgusting.  Similarly my black truffle pizza was gloppy, greasy and a little gross. Usually there is somewhat less cheese and it is a little more refined. I am awake at 4 am with a stomachache from it. Maybe the Monday night kitchen staff is junior league? The servers weren’t much better.  Actually, while this location is most convenient for us, I won’t be going back any time soon.

She regales me with stories about her youth in Italy.  She welcomes us by coming to the door & seating us personally.  She comes to the table to check up.  Regarding children - I've brought a few Nieces & nephews & grand nieces & she's utterly gracious & accomadating! I recommend Serafina on 105th Street 100% - especially the tuna burger & the vegetables w the spaghetti squash! Enjoy! Bon Apiet

Had such a wonderful experience at this new Serafina. From the moment we walked in, the owner Nicholas greeted us at the door and we immediately felt at home. The atmosphere and environment was so welcoming and inviting. There were several of us so we tried a variety of dishes. The prosciutto and buffalo mozzarella were a great starter as was the tuna and salmon tartare. We all shared a pizza and it was so perfectly  made, I wished I had gotten my own. On to the pastas, and here I was skeptical as I can be quite hard to please when it comes to my pastas. Having tried the homemade lasagna, gnocchi and spaghetti with the fresh clams my palette was more than satisfied and I had a hard time deciding which was my favorite as they were all wonderful. Great portion size, perfectly cooked and full of flavor. I cannot wait to come back and try some other dishes. Not that there was room for dessert but we really wanted to try something so we settled on the cheese cake and tiramisu. Wow!!! Guaranteed these were homemade by a real Italian.  Already looking forward to going back.

I always forget this place exists on the upper UWS! We came here for dinner and were able to walk in without a reservation on a busy night and sit a group of 4 at the big communal table at the front of the restaurant. Recommend a res if you want a smaller table for just your group. Most of us got pastas - carbonara and gnocchi and lobster bowtie pasta, which were all great, and the tuna burger was also delicious. The French fries were stale/overcooked and too hardened to be enjoyable though. Service was excellent! Space is also pretty large so would be a good spot for a group.
